          <declname>W</declname>
        </param>
    <requiresclause>std::is_same_v&lt;T, int32_t&gt; || std::is_same_v&lt;T, int64_t&gt;    </requiresclause>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Truncate an integer v, either int32_t or int64_t, to v - (v % W). </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The remainder, v % W, must be positive. For languages where % can produce negative values, the correct truncate function is: v - (((v % W) + W) % W) </para>
        </detaileddescription>
